text:

Wilder started throwing more jabs in the fourth round, and finally landed his powerful haymaker halfway through the fifth round. He earned a knock down before Washington came back. Wilder then threw a flurry of punches, and Washington simply could not defend himself enough to allow the referee to continue. 
"I want to tell y'all right now, I said I wasn't going nowhere, and I'm still here," Wilder said on the Fox telecast after the match. "I'm not going nowhere. We're going to keep them coming." 
Wilder was then asked whether he would face WBO heavyweight-title holder Joshua Parker, who was in attendance at Legacy Arena in Birmingham. 
"I'm ready for Joseph Parker," Wilder said. "The only question is, 'Are they ready for me?' I've done my part, Joseph Parker. Now it's your time to do yours." Watch This
